7:
—it was SO CRAZY! Even before we
got to the Palace of Stars!
11:
First, Luca got all scary! Then Amelia
grew TENTACLES! And Denah? She
punched the king!
16:
And Soushiro... He sliced up a literal
god! Oh! And Suizen looked SO.
CUTE. He had these ADORABLE ears
and a little tail, and—
25:
I'm not imagining anything! This
really happened, I swear!
30:
*sigh*... So, you've got a taste for
adventure now. And you're joinin' the
Abyss Exploration Team again?
34:
Yep! This'll be my third time, but it's
just gonna be a short trip. The real
adventure is after that!
39:
...Children your age go to school,
correct? "High school," was it? What
about you?
43:
Oh, yeah... Actually, I already had a
talk with my parents and teacher
about that stuff.
49:
I'm not gonna go to high school! I'm
gonna go save the world!
58:
All right... Next time, I'm coming with
you.
61:
I broke our last promise, and you
can bet I won't break it again.
65:
Our... promise? But you brought
Yumu back! He survived!
69:
Yeah, but... he went and got himself
killed, too!
74:
Indeed. I will never forget that
moment, not until the day I die...
78:
He's alive now, and that's what
matters! You kept your promise,
Nimbus!
82:
All right, all right... But we still need to
talk about YOU. Reckless, rash...
You're worse than your brother
sometimes!
93:
You believe anything can be
resolved by pushing through with
reckless abandon, do you not?
97:
Wh-what, me? Please... That's soooo
ridiculous. Heheh...
103:
What's that pirate lady been
teaching you, anyway?! I'm tellin' ya,
it's her fault... I have half a mind to
go join you on this scouting trip, too.
107:
Now HOLD ON! That's being a bit
overprotective, don't you think?!
111:
Believe me, I'm fine! Besides, it's just
a scouting mission! How dangerous
could it be?
119:
Woo-hoo! We are on FIRE. Everyone
wants a piece of us!
123:
More parasitic Devourers coming in.
We should probably do something
about that.
128:
That's not good. We'll never make it
to Nao's graduation on time if we
don't hurry it up!
148:
We've got no choice! Luca, send a
telepathic message to Couette!
We'll eject Nao and have Couette
collect her while we act as bait!
169:
May the wings of darkness carry you
to ever greater heights!
Congratulations!
177:
Don't worry! We'll totally make it to
the afterparty. You go and enjoy
yourself, okay?
190:
Nao Nagihara, present and
accounted for! I'm back from my
mission and RIGHT on time!
205:
*sigh*... I guess this is it. My two little
babies, all grown up...
209:
Feeling like a regular Rip Van Winkle
here. Feels like only yesterday that
you were learning how to walk...
214:
Sorry, Dad. I'm old enough to drink
now.
218:
Hey, at least you managed to get
well enough to see us graduate!
Thanks, Mom and Dad.
223: Can I, uh... talk with you?
240: Sorry for the wait! I'm all good now.
248:
Ayumu and your dad seem on edge.
You're not gonna tell them?
259:
That really took me by surprise. You
know, I never really thought about
him that way.
263:
So, I ended up just telling him that...
and he said, "Why don't we just test
it out?"
267:
That took me by surprise too, in a
weird way... I told him I'd think about
it.
271:
H-hmm... Well, I'd like to think that
there's no "right" or "wrong" answer
when it comes to relationships... I
think.
274:
But yeah, it might be tough if you
had to break up with him after the
fact, so... yeah, it'd be tough.
281: But yeah, still... I feel bad for Yuto.
285:
Who knows? Maybe you can pull off
being a femme fatale... Tell me all of
the juicy details if you do, okay?
290: There's no way I could do that!
294:
Yeah... Adventuring is the one and
only love I need!
297:
Still... I guess it wouldn't hurt being a
little nicer to Yumu.
